US OPEN
September 7, 2002
Richard Gasquet
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
THE MODERATOR:  Questions, please.  
 
 
Q.  How do you feel about your match today?  What went well?  How did you turn it around after that? 
 
RICHARD GASQUET:  My opponent has played very good.  He won 6-3, so 6-3, 5-4.  I can't win this match.  At 5-4, he played bad, yeah.  He was scared, and I won. 
 
Q.  Compared to the French Open Juniors, was there a lot more attention around you because you are French and you had been in the main draw also? 
 
RICHARD GASQUET:  Yes.  There were more attention in Roland Garros, but it's normal because here it is in United States.  
 
Q.  You were down two matchpoints.  What were you thinking when you were down matchpoint? 
 
RICHARD GASQUET:  I believe that I lost because he played very good.  I was lucky.  
 
Q.  You played attacking shots.  You hit a forehand and a backhand shot. 
 
RICHARD GASQUET:  Yeah, I was lucky.  
 
Q.  You were lucky?
 
RICHARD GASQUET:  Yeah.  
 
Q.  You didn't wait for him to attack. 
 
RICHARD GASQUET:  Yes.  
 

